law.text:
As used in KRS 363.900 to 363.908, unless the context clearly requires otherwise:
"ASTM standard" means the latest standards and specifications as set forth by the American Society for Testing and Materials in accordance with the most recent version of ASTM specifications for automotive gasoline, or ASTM specifications for diesel fuel oils;
"Commissioner" means the Commissioner of Agriculture or a departmental employee designated by the Commissioner to act on his behalf for the purposes of KRS 363.900 to 363.908;
"Department" means the Kentucky Department of Agriculture;
"Diesel fuel" means refined oil commonly used in internal combustion engines and defined as diesel fuel under the ASTM standard classification of diesel fuel oils;
"Division" means the Division of Regulation and Inspection in the Kentucky Department of Agriculture;
"Gasoline" means gasoline as defined in KRS 138.210;
"Motor fuel" means any product used for the generation of power in an internal combustion or turbine engine and includes gasoline, diesel fuel, or gasoline-alcohol blend fuels; and
"Retail facility" means a facility that sells motor fuels to the general public.
